        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Philada.</placeName>
                <date>Feb. 11/62</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev Mr. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Noticing in this<lb/> mornings inquirer an<del>d</del> answer
                to<lb/> your article of this week and think<lb/>ing that I could give you a
                little<lb/> information on the subject, I thought<lb/> it best to <sic>addres</sic>
                a few lines to<lb/> you in regard to it. One of the two<lb/> adults that was
                baptized in <date>1858</date>,<lb/> I was acquainted with, this young<lb/> Man lived
                with the <persName>Rev. Dr.<lb/> Newman</persName>, for the space of three<lb/>
                months at the Doctors expense<lb/> who fitted him out with a<lb/> new suit of
                clothes and pocket<lb/> money; at the end of which<lb/> time he was baptized, then
                the<lb/> Doctor gave 100 Dollars and a<lb/> letter to recommendation to the<lb/>
                firm of <persName>Bunn<add>?</add> Raiquel &amp; Co.</persName></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>who sold about $150 worth of<lb/> goods on Credit after this he<lb/> swindled them
                all out of their<lb/> money and goods, the name of<lb/> this young man now escapes
                me<lb/> but I think if it is necessary<lb/> I can ascertain it. <sic>Hopeing</sic>
                these<lb/> few lines may be a source of<lb/> information to you in order to<lb/>
                carry on your controversy I<lb/> remain yours respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Louis Potsdamer</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>331 Market St.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
